---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Stats
description: CECS Faculty Senate committee service by the numbers — representation by department, role, term, and renewal timeline.
permalink: /stats/
---
{% set t = stats.totals %}

<section class="page-head">
  <h1>CECS service by the numbers</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    A live snapshot of College of Engineering and Computer Science representation across
    UCF Faculty Senate committees for {{ committees.academicYear }}. Everything here is
    derived automatically from the
    <a href="{{ '/committees/' | url }}">committee catalog</a>{% if stats.hasVolunteers %} and volunteer sign-ups{% endif %}.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="stat-cards" aria-label="Headline numbers">
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-num">{{ t.committees }}</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Committees tracked</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-num">{{ t.seatsFilled }}</span>
    <span class="stat-label">CECS seats filled</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card{% if t.openSeats %} stat-card-open{% endif %}">
    <span class="stat-num">{{ t.openSeats }}</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Open seat{{ 's' if t.openSeats != 1 }} to fill</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-num">{{ t.distinctFaculty }}</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Faculty serving</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-num">{{ t.departmentsRepresented }}</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Departments represented</span>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-card">
    <span class="stat-num">{{ t.coveragePct }}%</span>
    <span class="stat-label">Seat coverage</span>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="section-head">
    <h2>Representation by department</h2>
    <span class="muted">{{ t.seatsFilled }} seat{{ 's' if t.seatsFilled != 1 }} · {{ t.distinctFaculty }} faculty</span>
  </div>
  {% if stats.byDepartment | length %}
    <div class="chart">
      {% for d in stats.byDepartment %}
        <div class="chart-row">
          <span class="chart-label" title="{{ d.name }}">{{ d.name }}</span>
          <span class="chart-track">
            <span class="chart-bar" style="width: {{ d.seats | barPct(stats.maxDeptSeats) }}%"></span>
          </span>
          <span class="chart-value">
            {{ d.seats }}
            <small>{{ d.people }} {{ 'person' if d.people == 1 else 'people' }} · {{ d.committees }} committee{{ 's' if d.committees != 1 }}{% if d.volunteerPeople %} · {{ d.volunteerPeople }} volunteered{% endif %}</small>
          </span>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="hint">Bars show the number of committee seats each CECS department currently holds. A department can hold more seats than it has people when one person serves on multiple committees.</p>
  {% else %}
    <p class="empty">No department representation recorded yet.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section>
  <div class="section-head">
    <h2>Representation relative to department size</h2>
    <span class="muted">Bigger units are expected to hold more seats</span>
  </div>
  <p class="category-blurb">
    Raw seat counts favor large departments. These bars normalize by department size
    (ECE&nbsp;=&nbsp;CS&nbsp;=&nbsp;MAE&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;CECE&nbsp;=&nbsp;IEMS&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;MSE&nbsp;=&nbsp;SMST):
    a <strong>parity index</strong> compares each unit's share of CECS seats to its share of
    faculty size. <strong>1.0&times;</strong> is exactly proportional — below that a department
    is under-represented for its size and is a natural recruiting target.
  </p>
  <div class="chart parity-chart">
    {% for d in stats.byNormalizedSize %}
      <div class="chart-row">
        <span class="chart-label" title="{{ d.name }}">{{ d.abbr }}</span>
        <span class="chart-track parity-track">
          <span class="parity-baseline" aria-hidden="true" style="left: {{ 1 | barPct(stats.maxParity) }}%"></span>
          <span class="chart-bar {% if d.parity < 1 %}parity-under{% else %}parity-over{% endif %}" style="width: {{ d.parity | barPct(stats.maxParity) }}%"></span>
        </span>
        <span class="chart-value">
          {{ d.parity }}&times;
          <small>{{ d.seats }} of {{ d.expectedSeats }} expected · size {{ d.size }}{% if d.volunteers %} · {{ d.volunteers }} volunteered{% endif %}</small>
        </span>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="hint">
    Parity index = (department's share of filled seats) ÷ (department's share of faculty size).
    The dashed line marks 1.0× parity. "Expected" seats are what perfectly proportional
    representation would give each unit at the current total, rounded to the nearest whole seat.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="stat-split">
  <div>
    <div class="section-head"><h2>By seat role</h2></div>
    {% if stats.byRole | length %}
      <ul class="stat-list">
        {% for r in stats.byRole %}
          <li><span class="stat-list-label">{{ r.name }}</span><span class="stat-pill">{{ r.count }}</span></li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    {% else %}
      <p class="empty">No roles recorded.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="section-head"><h2>By term length</h2></div>
    {% if stats.byTermLength | length %}
      <ul class="stat-list">
        {% for term in stats.byTermLength %}
          <li><span class="stat-list-label">{{ term.name }}</span><span class="stat-pill">{{ term.count }} committee{{ 's' if term.count != 1 }}</span></li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    {% else %}
      <p class="empty">No term data recorded.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>

{% if stats.termTimeline | length %}
  <section>
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2>Seat renewal timeline</h2>
      <span class="muted">When current CECS terms expire</span>
    </div>
    <div class="chart">
      {% for y in stats.termTimeline %}
        <div class="chart-row">
          <span class="chart-label">{{ y.year }}</span>
          <span class="chart-track">
            <span class="chart-bar chart-bar-alt" style="width: {{ y.count | barPct(stats.maxTimeline) }}%"></span>
          </span>
          <span class="chart-value">{{ y.count }} seat{{ 's' if y.count != 1 }}</span>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="hint">Seats whose terms end in each year. Years with several expirations are where recruiting will matter most.</p>
  </section>
{% endif %}

{% if stats.multiCommittee | length %}
  <section>
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2>Serving on multiple committees</h2>
      <span class="muted">{{ stats.multiCommittee | length }} faculty</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="volunteer-list multi-list">
      {% for p in stats.multiCommittee %}
        <li>
          <strong>{{ p.name }}</strong> <span class="stat-pill">{{ p.count }} committees</span>
          {% if p.department %}<br /><span class="muted">{{ p.department }}</span>{% endif %}
          <br /><span class="muted">{{ p.committees | join(' · ') }}</span>
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </section>
{% endif %}

<section class="band">
  <h2>Want to move these numbers?</h2>
  <p>
    {% if t.openSeats %}
      There {{ 'is' if t.openSeats == 1 else 'are' }} <strong>{{ t.openSeats }} open CECS seat{{ 's' if t.openSeats != 1 }}</strong>
      across {{ t.committeesWithOpenSeats }} committee{{ 's' if t.committeesWithOpenSeats != 1 }}. Adding your name takes a couple of minutes.
    {% else %}
      Every CECS seat is currently filled — but backups are always welcome for mid-year openings.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
  <p class="hero-actions">
    <a class="btn btn-large" href="{{ '/signup/' | url }}">Volunteer</a>
    <a class="btn btn-large btn-ghost" href="{{ '/volunteers/' | url }}">See who's volunteered</a>
    <a class="btn btn-large btn-ghost" href="{{ '/committees/' | url }}">Browse committees</a>
  </p>
</section>

{% if stats.generatedAt %}
  <p class="muted">Volunteer figures last synced {{ stats.generatedAt | readableDate }}. Committee figures reflect the current catalog. Always confirm against the <a href="{{ site.committeesReferenceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official UCF Faculty Senate listing ↗</a>.</p>
{% else %}
  <p class="muted">Figures reflect the current committee catalog. Always confirm against the <a href="{{ site.committeesReferenceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official UCF Faculty Senate listing ↗</a>.</p>
{% endif %}
